Key Match Events: Devin Booker returned to play after missing five games due to a left groin strain.
Booker had a game-high nine assists despite a poor shooting performance, going 4-20 from the field.
The Phoenix Suns lost to the Memphis Grizzlies 117-112.
Pre-Game Insights: Devin Booker was labeled as a 'game-time decision' but ended up playing in the game.
Post-Match Reflections: Head coach Mike Budenholzer praised Booker's playmaking and leadership, emphasizing his importance to the team.
Booker expressed his relief and happiness to be back on the court after his injury.
Booker acknowledged the challenge of returning from injury and the need to knock off the rust.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Bradley Beal was ruled out of the game due to a left hip contusion.
